{"componentChunkName":"component---src-page-post-tsx","path":"/mvps-in-production","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Markus Tacker","tagLine":"Software Crafter","description":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at Nordic Semiconductor.‚Äã\n\t\tMentor. Speaker. ‚ÄãConference & Community builder. Camper. üèïÔ∏è üöê","gitHubUrl":"https://github.com/coderbyheart/coderbyheart.com.git","siteUrl":"https://coderbyheart.com","twitter":"@coderbyheart","defaultCard":"https://images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/3Jk4P6nFPNzaz1gsguktk8/350b7e4ddb2c7d86416243d9902920e2/social-card-default-2020.png"}}},"pageContext":{"page":{"id":"e761e287-0d3e-575b-b768-6a93d052b0ec","name":"mvps-in-production","relativeDirectory":"post","relativePath":"post/mvps-in-production.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"properties":{"src":"//images.ctfassets.net/bncv3c2gt878/2TLqVCHxsX9CQjHK64rwcn/33621aa422b3b9432f8cc077c78d193b/2017-06-10-mvps-in-production.jpg?w=3039&h=2014","alt":"Driving on the Autobahn at Night"},"children":[],"tagName":"img","type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"From 2013 to 2017 I've worked as a CTO in four startups:\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"DeinBus"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://www.deinbus.de/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"dotHIV"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://click4life.hiv/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":",\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Fintura"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://fintura.de/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", and\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Resourceful Humans"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://resourceful-humans.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":". In all I was not a\ntechnical co-founder but joined the team at a time when the existing technology\nshowed cracks that put the business at risk. The notorious shortage of tech\ntalent made these startups turn to freelancers, agencies to build their first\npublic beta or despite lacking a professional technical background the founders\nstarted to build the solution on their own. Which is actually the smartest thing\nyou can do, because in the pre-seed phase of a startup cash is usually a very\nscarce resources and freelancers and agencies are charging rates which are not\naffordable on a sustainable rate, but will lead to cutting (cost) corners that\ncreate technical debt that is not transparent to the startup, which leads to\neven more risks."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Once I joined these teams my job in all cases was to stabilize the technology\nand make it more robust and reliable, and increase the headcount of the tech\nteam to improve "},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"velocity"}],"tagName":"em","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":", which is the speed at which you can release new\nfeatures to your (sometimes paying) users. In a start-up environment, where\nthere are only known and unknown unknowns achiving these goals is especially\nchallenging. In this blog series I'll explain the principles that I've employed\nwhich enable notoriously understaffed tech teams to tackle these challenges at a\nsustainable pace."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"This is a recollection of how I made it work, and of course, so many things\ncould have been done better, if the circumstances had been different. The\nopinions expressed in these posts are solely my personal views and not those of\nmy former employers."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I'll try to put this into an easy to read guide for future CTOs,\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"follow me on Twitter"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://twitter.com/coderbyheart","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" to know first, when\nI'll finish a new section."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Before you start reading here is some context: all these startups were product\nstartups building web-based (an mobile) applications, which were development\nin-house as well as using service providers and freelancers. We hosted them on\nbare-metal, virtual serves or on AWS. The team size was never more then 15\npeople, always in a distributed setting, where working remotely was the norm."}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The first post is already finished:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Setting up a product management process"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"/setting-up-a-product-management-process/"},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ul","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Coming up next:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Building an architecture that supports feature creep, Building features in\nverticals"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ul","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"I'll also want cover these topics in later installements of this series:"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Going serverless"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Push to deploy and Code Stewardship"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Running experiments in production, without staging"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"The case for JavaScript"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Test-driven development"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Designing RESTful APIs that evolve easily"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Using Bots and open-source to fight Conway's law"}],"tagName":"li","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"tagName":"ul","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"But here is the catch:"}],"tagName":"strong","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":" I want 10 additional readers to sign up for my\ninfluencer group for this series before I start the third section, and you'll\nget to pick which one I'll continue with!"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"},{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Fill out this form if you are interested to read more!"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://coderbyheart.typeform.com/to/wxURIj","target":"_blank","rel":["nofollow","noreferrer"]},"type":"element"}],"tagName":"p","properties":{},"type":"element"}],"type":"root","data":{"quirksMode":false}},"frontmatter":{"title":"MVPs in Production","subtitle":"Reflections on being a CTO for 5 years","noheadline":null,"date":"2017-06-10T13:45+02:00","abstract":"In this post series I'll reflect on the technical principles that I've employed in the last 5 years working as a CTO to achieve something that would have been seen as futile and insane a decade ago, but is the norm today: running software in production that is neither complete nor well-designed and needs to evolve every day.","lang":null},"headings":[]}},"Footer":{"id":"cfe5b9e2-511c-5615-992a-dab82e1f8ed7","name":"Footer","relativeDirectory":"","relativePath":"Footer.md","remark":{"htmlAst":{"children":[{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Software Crafter building üå©Ô∏è cloud-based cellular IoT solutions at\n"},{"children":[{"children":[],"type":"text","value":"Nordic Semiconductor"}],"tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"https://nordicsemi.com/","target":"_blank","rel":["nof